text:
Everyday outfit of Alfred, crown prince of Firene. Made for ease of 
movement, and includes a fresh flower from Firene pinned to the breast.

Everyday outfit of Anna, merchant extraordinaire. This chunky knit dress 
and scarf ward off the cold of even the snowiest of days.

Glasses that safely block the sun's glare. The large design covers both 
eyes, and the tinted lenses can be useful when going incognito.

The heavy, thick frames can be painful on the ears if worn for a long time, 
but some say the striking effect on their image is worth it.

Everyday outfit of Bunet, Prince Fogado's retainer. He's worn it daily 
since his time in the canteen, so it must be washed frequently.

Everyday outfit of Boucheron, Prince Alfred's retainer. The buttons seem 
to be on the verge of snapping off, but they've held out this long.

Clothing worn by Brodian commoners. Made for practicality, the fabric is 
easily washable and the colors don't show stains. (Two versions.)

Clothing worn by Brodian commoners. Made for practicality, the fabric is 
washable and the colors don't show stains. The clasp is faux horn.

Clothing worn by Brodian commoners. Made for practicality, the fabric is 
washable and the colors don't show stains. The fluffy trim is removable.

Clothing worn by Brodian commoners. The traditional design is trimmed 
with alpaca wool and is extremely warm. (Two versions.)

Clothing worn by Brodian commoners. The traditional design is trimmed 
with alpaca wool for warmth. The shoes resist slipping on cliffs.

Clothing worn by Brodian commoners. The traditional design is trimmed 
with alpaca wool for warmth. Often worn by nomadic people of Brodia.

Brodian clothing sent as a token of friendship. Made with sturdy materials, 
this outfit prioritizes comfort and design. Pattern is said to ward off evil.

Brodian clothing sent as a token of friendship. Made with sturdy materials 
and imitation bear fur, this outfit prioritizes comfort and design.

Clothing worn by Brodian nobles. The outfit is embroidered with thread 
from Brodia's productive gold mines. (Two versions.)

Clothing worn by Brodian nobles. Trimmed with faux fur and embroidered 
with gold thread, with a black hem made of stain-resistant material.

Clothing worn by Brodian nobles. Trimmed with faux fur and embroidered 
with gold thread, the jacket's shorter length enables ease of movement.

Clothing worn by Brodian nobles, usually at festive events, this design 
features a Brodian flower symbolizing fortitude. (Two versions.)

Clothing worn by Brodian nobles, usually at festive events. This design 
features a Brodian flower symbolizing fortitude. The skirt is quite heavy.

Clothing worn by Brodian nobles. Made with very thick and warm fabric, 
the design features a Brodian flower symbolizing fortitude.

Brodian clothes sent as a token of friendship. White faux leather 
symbolizes hope. Some people order wedding attire made from it.

Brodian clothing sent as a token of friendship. White faux leather 
symbolizes hope. The decorative pattern is actually the craftsman's crest.

Everyday outfit of Céline, princess of Firene. The ribbons provide the 
perfect touch of elegance for teatime, and the jewel is the color of honey.

Everyday outfit of Chloé, Princess Céline's retainer. Though she often 
wears it to visit food stalls, she takes care not to dirty it when she eats.

Everyday outfit of Citrinne, Prince Alcryst's retainer. The jacket is made 
with quality faux fur, and the charms of a noble house adorn the belt.

Everyday outfit of Clanne, 33rd Steward of the Dragon. Has a special 
pocket in the outer layer to hide emergency snacks.

Sweet sunglasses with gradient brown lenses. They're popular with 
fashion-conscious folks who also want some protection from the sun.

Based on Byleth, the Emblem of the Academy. A mercenary who became 
a teacher.

Based on Celica, the Emblem of Echoes. The princess of a 
vibrant country.

Based on Eirika, the Emblem of the Sacred. A princess who takes up her 
sword for the sake of peace.

Based on Ike, the Emblem of Radiance. A famous mercenary leader 
with unparalleled skill in battle.

Based on Corrin, the Emblem of Fates. A royal whose blood is that 
of the First Dragons.

Based on Leif, the Emblem of Genealogy. A brave prince in whose veins 
runs the blood of two crusaders.

Based on Lyn, the Emblem of Blazing. A virtuoso swordswoman from a 
nomadic tribe that lived in nature.

Based on Lucina, the Emblem of Awakening. A royal heir who knows 
anything can change and will not yield to despair.
Based on Marth, the Emblem of Beginnings. A hero among heroes.

Based on Micaiah, the Emblem of Dawn. A priestess with 
mysterious powers.
Based on Roy, the Emblem of Binding. A brave and intelligent noble.

Based on Sigurd, the Emblem of the Holy War. A noble knight with a 
mighty lineage.

Everyday outfit of Diamant, crown prince of Brodia. It is made from 
material that can withstand virtually anything in case of emergencies.

Everyday outfit of Etie, Prince Alfred's retainer. Marked by the frills on 
the sleeves and skirt. The design on the hem matches her battle outfit.

Clothes designed at the boutique specially for training, made in a unique 
style. The material is durable and naturally wicks away moisture.

Used to hide a single eye, this accessory is said to have originated in 
Brodia when soldiers sought to mask their injuries on the battlefield.

A mask chiefly worn to Firenese masquerades, where people from all 
walks of life can mingle together anonymously.

Clothing worn by Firenese commoners. Often the first garment made by 
Firenese children when they learn to sew. (Two versions.)

Clothing worn by Firenese commoners. Often the first garment made by 
novice Firenese tailors. Children enjoy crafting the floral bows.

Clothing worn by Firenese commoners. Often the first garment made by 
novice Firenese tailors. They say making the vest is the trickiest part.

Clothing worn by Firenese commoners. This casual attire is decorated in a 
popular pattern said to show off one's personality. (Two versions.)

Clothing worn by Firenese commoners. A pattern popular in Firene 
decorates an apron that doubles as a handkerchief.

Clothing worn by Firenese commoners. The vest is accented with 
a pattern popular in Firene said to show off one's personality.

Firenese clothing sent as a token of friendship. The traditional floral 
embroidery represents affection for loved ones.

Firenese clothing sent as a token of friendship. The traditional floral 
embroidery represents affection for loved ones.

Clothing worn by Firenese nobles. The bright blue color is the result of 
heavy dyes and represents an abundant harvest. (Two versions.)

Clothing worn by Firenese nobles. Composed of a light skirt of sturdy 
fabric, dyed blue to represent the skies that bless the harvest.

Clothing worn by Firenese nobles. Composed of a vest with heavy blue 
dyes representing the skies that bless the harvest.

Clothing worn by Firenese nobles. Marked by a gradient attained through 
traditional Firenese hand-dyeing techniques. (Two versions.)

Clothing worn by Firenese nobles. Features a gradient achieved through 
traditional Firenese dyeing techniques. Often worn on festive occasions.

Clothing worn by Firenese nobles. Features a gradient achieved through 
traditional Firenese dyeing techniques, accented with a fresh flower.

Traditional Firenese clothing sent as a symbol of friendship. The pattern 
signifies a hope for peace and the sash represents unbreakable bonds.

Traditional Firenese clothing sent as a symbol of friendship. The intricate 
design signifies a prayer for peace. Often worn when entertaining guests.

Everyday outfit of Fogado, prince of Solm. He often uses the scarf to 
mask his face when his identity is on the verge of being discovered.

Everyday outfit of Framme, 33rd Steward of the Dragon. Has a special 
pocket in the outer layer to hide emergency snacks.

Everyday outfit of Goldmary, Princess Hortensia's retainer. She apologizes 
every chance she gets for its overly pristine condition.

Everyday outfit of Hortensia, princess of Elusia. Partly inspired by Ivy's 
clothes, this outfit is optimized for maximum cuteness in every inch.

Clothing worn by Elusian commoners. Deep-green fabrics can camouflage 
the wearer in the depths of the woods. (Two versions.)

Clothing worn by Elusian commoners. Deep-green fabrics can camouflage 
the wearer in the woods. The scarf features Elusia's oldest design.

Clothing worn by Elusian commoners. Deep-green fabrics can camouflage 
the wearer in the depths of the woods. Frequently worn by lumberjacks.

Clothing worn by Elusian commoners. Four colors of fabric are woven 
into a pattern thought to bring good luck. (Two versions.)

Clothing worn by Elusian commoners. Four colors of fabric are woven 
into a pattern thought to bring good luck. The scarf is unexpectedly long.

Clothing worn by Elusian commoners. Four colors of fabric are woven 
into a pattern thought to bring good luck. Quite popular in springtime.

Elusian clothing sent as a token of friendship. The vivid turquoise color 
is achieved with enchanted dye made from the bark of coniferous trees.

Elusian clothing sent as a token of friendship. The design features ancient 
symbols that represent the magical power and beauty of Elusia.

Clothing worn by Elusian nobles. Fine garments lined with thick fleece 
to keep out wind and snow. (Two versions.)

Clothing worn by Elusian nobles. Fine garments lined with thick fleece 
to keep out wind and snow. The decorative lace is often made by hand.

Clothing worn by Elusian nobles. Fine garments lined with thick fleece 
to keep out cold. The coat is warm enough to allow light inner layers.

Clothing worn by Elusian nobles. The traditional technique of knitting 
multiple layers for each coat takes several months. (Two versions.)

Clothing worn by Elusian nobles. The laborious process of knitting many 
layers per coat sometimes leads to a waiting period lasting several years.

Clothing worn by Elusian nobles. The coat is knit in multiple layers, and 
the resulting fabric is so dense that it protects against rain and snow.

Elusian clothing sent as a token of friendship. Gold thread and faux fur 
represent starry skies. The quality is beyond anything available at market.

Elusian clothing sent as a token of friendship. Gold thread and faux fur 
represent starry skies. The quality matches what is seen in museums.

Everyday outfit of Ivy, crown princess of Elusia. She developed it through 
painstaking trial and error to be comfortable enough to wear in the cold.

Everyday outfit of Jade, Prince Diamant's retainer. The outfit is easy to 
move around in and supported by a sturdy leather belt for posture.

Everyday outfit of Jean, doctor in training. The left pocket contains 
medicinal herbs, while the right one is where he keeps his notes for study.

Everyday outfit of Kagetsu, Princess Ivy's retainer. The rice-ball design on 
the pants features cod roe, salmon, pickled plum, and bonito flakes.

Everyday outfit of Lapis, Prince Alcryst's retainer. She's treasured this 
apron, with its floral designs and shoulder straps, for a very long time.

Everyday outfit of Lindon, elderly sage of Elusia. He never removes the 
silver pendant around his neck, ensuring that it's always close at hand.

Clothing worn by Lythian clerics, daily and to church. The fine patterning 
pays homage to the Divine Dragon. (Two versions.)

Clothing worn by Lythian clerics, daily and to church. The fine patterning, 
paying homage to the Divine Dragon, is sewn only by the pure of heart.

Clothing worn by Lythian clerics, daily and to church. The fine patterning 
and gold embroidery pay homage to the Divine Dragon.

Clothing worn by Lythian clerics. The technique for making fabric reflect 
light and shine is found only on Lythos. (Two versions.)

Clothing worn by Lythian clerics. The technique to make reflective fabric 
is known only on Lythos. Suitable for special events, not manual labor.

Clothing worn by Lythian clerics. The technique to make reflective fabric 
is known only on Lythos. Despite appearances, the fabric is soft.

Clothing worn by Lythian clerics. The fabric is said to embody the power 
of the Divine Dragon. The pattern symbolizes harmony. (Two versions.)

Clothing worn by Lythian clerics. The fabric is said to embody the power 
of the Divine Dragon. The pattern is meant to honor casualties of war.

Clothing worn by Lythian clerics. The fabric is said to embody the power 
of the Divine Dragon. The pattern symbolizes respect for the Emblems.

Everyday outfit of Louis, Princess Céline's retainer. The sleeves are made 
to be rolled up, allowing him to offer perfect service at a moment's notice.

These frames were crafted to stay out of the way when looking up. 
They're popular with people who want to show off their eyes.

Everyday outfit reserved specially for the Divine Dragon's child. 
Specially tailored to fit perfectly.

Everyday outfit reserved specially for the Divine Dragon's child. 
Specially tailored to fit perfectly.

Formal attire in the style of the Divine Dragon tailored especially for the 
guardian spirit, who wears this with pride and a hint of nostalgia.

This bell on a red and white cord feels like a lucky charm. 
It jingles merrily, making it fun to walk or run.

A butterfly landed on 's tail and refused to budge. It's 
stayed still for so long that no one can tell if it's even a real butterfly.

Dramatic eyebrows that bring facial communication to the next level. 
With these, you'll always know if is surprised.

A pair of fluffy, artificial wings that seem to float in the breeze. But watch 
out! The wearer may start to believe they can fly, so stay away from cliffs.

A crown woven with flowers from the meadow where likes 
to nap. The answer to the question, "What does tranquility smell like?"

This ribbon is so light that will forget it's there. To see the 
guardian spirit jump in surprise whenever it sees it is pure joy.

For the discerning guardian spirit, this dashing hat has a dignified flair. 
With this distinguished accessory, even posture seems to improve.

A must-have vacation item for looking chill in the summer heat. For the 
guardian spirit who wants to go from cute to cool with one accessory.

A wig styled to match . Setting aside whether it actually 
looks good, appears utterly delighted.

Everyday outfit of Mauvier, former member of the Four Hounds. Woven 
originally in Firene, he cares for it so meticulously that it appears new.

Everyday outfit of Merrin, Princess Timerra's retainer. Though the wolf's 
tail isn't real, she has it somehow rigged to wag when she's happy.

Everyday outfit of Timerra, crown princess of Solm. Its breathable fabric 
is surprisingly flameproof, making it perfect for sitting around a campfire.

Glasses are an adaptive device developed by the talented glaziers of 
Elusia. The lenses are polished to be as clear as ice.

Everyday outfit of Pandreo, Prince Fogado's retainer. He often wears it 
to parties, along with a simple stole for religious purposes.

Everyday outfit of Panette, Princess Timerra's retainer. She tore it while 
on a rampage and mended it herself with some colorful threads.

Everyday outfit of Rosado, Princess Hortensia's retainer. He personally 
altered this heirloom from his father to make it especially cute.

Everyday outfit of Saphir, royal knight of Brodia. The skirt is water- 
repellent, and she always removes the gloves before cleaning fish.

Everyday outfit of Seadall, dancer and fortune-teller. It's meant to 
enhance his reputation as a soothsayer, but it leaves his stomach cold.

A unique mask painted with a skull motif. Used in a Solmic festival in 
which the participants all decorate these masks with their own designs.

Clothing worn by Solmic commoners. A large piece of fabric is used to 
create the traditional wraps in this outfit. (Two versions.)

Clothing worn by Solmic commoners. A large piece of fabric is used to 
create the stylistic wraps. Some save their favorite colors for special days.

Clothing worn by Solmic commoners. It's a pastime in Solm to take 
friends out shopping for just the right fabric at a good price.

Clothing worn by Solmic commoners. Fabric patterned with Solmic motifs 
complements high-quality shoes that keep the feet cool. (Two versions.)

Clothing worn by Solmic commoners. Fabric patterned with Solmic motifs 
complements high-quality shoes that are ideal for long desert walks.

Clothing worn by Solmic commoners. Fabric patterned with Solmic motifs 
complements high-quality shoes that keep the feet cool on sand.

Solmic clothing sent as a token of affection to close friends. The dunes 
symbolize eternity and the dark weave represents connection.

Solmic clothing sent as a token of friendship. The dunes symbolize 
eternity and the dark weave represents connection. Good party outfit.

Clothing worn by Solmic nobles. Thin, breathable fabric ensures comfort 
even in Solm's hot climate. (Two versions.)

Clothing worn by Solmic nobles. Thin, breathable fabric ensures comfort 
even in Solm's hot climate. Comes with a robe to block out the sun.

Clothing worn by Solmic nobles. Thin breathable fabric ensures comfort 
even in Solm's hot climate. Cut to a length suitable for walking on sand.

Clothing worn by Solmic nobles. Often worn at parties. It is said that 
flashy clothes help one find "the road to paradise." (Two versions.)

Clothing worn by Solmic nobles. It is said that flashy clothes help one find 
"the road to paradise." Designed to look good while dancing at parties.

Clothing worn by Solmic nobles. It is said that flashy clothes help one find 
"the road to paradise." Popular for parties and sunrise walks in the desert.

Solmic clothing sent as a token of friendship. An imitation of the dress 
worn by a princess of legend, it is said the wearer will gain eternal wealth.

Solmic clothing sent as a token of friendship. Inspired by a famous legend, 
it is said the wearer will gain eternal wealth. It even sells well abroad.

Everyday outfit of Alcryst, prince of Brodia. While he sees only the 
differences with Diamant's outfit, the truth is they're quite similar.

Simple swimwear. Designed for swimming, training, and tanning, this is 
an outfit for working out and looking good doing it. (Two versions.)

Basic swimwear. Designed to provide a confidence boost while swimming, 
training, and tanning. The waist wrap comes in all kinds of colors.

Basic swimwear. Designed for swimming, training, and tanning. 
This outfit includes a necklace to help the wearer shine.

Swimwear that exposes relatively little skin. Meant for people who care 
most about function and comfort for activities. (Two versions.)

Basic swimwear. Comfortable and functional for activities, but prone to 
leaving distinctive tan lines when sunbathing.

Basic swimwear. Suitable for swimming, training, or sunbathing. 
The matching shirt is comfortable and designed to dry quickly.

Colorful swimwear for expressive youths. A design likely to leave an 
impression. (Two versions.)

Highly ornamented swimwear for youths. The delightful ribbon on the 
front is surprisingly well-secured.

Highly ornamented swimwear for youths. Fresh tropical flowers that never 
seem to wilt adorn the garland.

Everyday outfit of Amber, Prince Diamant's retainer. The embroidery on 
the back and breast is modeled after the alpacas of his hometown.

Everyday outfit worn by Vander, 32nd Steward of the Dragon. 
He's rumored to have several identical uniforms just like it.

Everyday outfit for Veyle, daughter of the Fell Dragon. She pays little 
attention to her attire, so her fashion-conscious friends chose this outfit.

Everyday outfit of Yunaka, eccentric thief. She fashioned this chic outfit 
from ordinary garments bought around town.

Everyday outfit of Zelkov, Princess Ivy's retainer. The purpose of the 
multiple belts is unclear, but the key is known to be purely decorative.
